        "client_msg_id": "7b60aa80-4e9e-415c-a9d9-532d5948eead",
        "text": "Hello again, I hope everyone has had a great month since the Sprint!\n\nSome of you might remember, I was tackling one of Luke Tierney’s issues, adding the ability to add alternative communications backends for R’s parallel package.\n\nA bug report <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18587> was raised during the Sprint and (partially) adopted thereafter in R-devel.\n\nI have now implemented a full parallel backend in my CRAN package ‘mirai’.\n\nIt has just landed in the development version at <https:\/\/github.com\/shikokuchuo\/mirai> and may be installed from R-universe using:\n\n```install.packages(\"mirai\", repos = \"shikokuchuo.r-universe.dev\")```\n`mirai::make_cluster()`  creates a ‘miraiCluster’ and this can then be used with all the cluster apply functions in the parallel package.\n\nIf any of you use `parLapply()` and friends and run R-devel, I would be grateful for any testing using the new ‘miraiCluster’ to help find bugs and corner cases.\n\nThanks!",
